      "img": "https://cdn.langeek.co/photo/32094/original/?type=jpeg",
      "pronunciation": "ˈbaɪɫ",
      "senses": [
        {
          "definition": "a greenish-brown alkaline fluid that is produced by the liver in order to help the body digest fats",
          "examples": [
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Bile is a digestive fluid produced by the liver and stored in the gallbladder, released into the small intestine to aid in the digestion of fats."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The greenish-yellow color of bile is due to the presence of bilirubin, a waste product from the breakdown of red blood cells."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Bile salts in bile help emulsify fats, breaking them down into smaller droplets that can be more easily digested by enzymes."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Blockage of the bile ducts can lead to a buildup of bile in the liver, causing jaundice and impairing digestion."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "After a fatty meal, the gallbladder contracts, releasing bile into the duodenum to facilitate the digestion and absorption of dietary fats."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
