              "cf": "",
              "x": "The esophagus is a muscular tube that connects the throat to the stomach, allowing food and liquids to pass from the mouth to the stomach for digestion."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "When you swallow food or drink, it travels down the esophagus through a series of muscle contractions called peristalsis."
