      "senses": [
        {
          "definition": "(anatomy) the main part of the large intestine, between the caecum to the rectum, where water is removed from solid waste",
          "examples": [
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The colon, also known as the large intestine, is the final portion of the digestive tract responsible for absorbing water and electrolytes from undigested food matter."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The colon plays a crucial role in forming feces by compacting waste material and eliminating it from the body through the rectum."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The colon is divided into several segments, including the ascending colon, transverse colon, descending colon, and sigmoid colon."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Disorders of the colon, such as diverticulitis, ulcerative colitis, and colorectal cancer, can cause abdominal pain, changes in bowel habits, and other symptoms."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "A colonoscopy is a procedure used to examine the colon for abnormalities, such as polyps or tumors, and to screen for colorectal cancer."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
