        {
          "definition": "a large gland in the body that produces insulin and glucagon and substances that help the body digest food",
          "examples": [
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The pancreas is a gland located behind the stomach that plays a crucial role in digestion and blood sugar regulation."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The pancreas produces digestive enzymes that are released into the small intestine to break down carbohydrates, proteins, and fats."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Insulin and glucagon, hormones produced by the pancreas, help regulate blood sugar levels by controlling the uptake and release of glucose."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Pancreatitis is a condition characterized by inflammation of the pancreas, often caused by gallstones, alcohol consumption, or certain medications."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "The islets of Langerhans within the pancreas contain beta cells that produce insulin, essential for glucose metabolism and energy production in the body."
            }
